refactor: refresh compatibility injection with new modules
- Update compatibility injection to include new modules civitai_gallery_action, prompt_ui, and ishortcut_action while removing legacy recipe_action, classification_action, scan_action, model, ishortcut, recipe, classification, and util modules.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: add job report and unify UV run in startup scripts
- Add comprehensive job report for bug fix #034 detailing the uv virtual-environment execution repair - Refactor Windows start.bat to detect uv availability, prefer uv run for dependency installation and script execution, and retain pip/venv fallback with unified logging - Update bash start.sh to check for uv, use exec uv run for automatic environment handling, streamline fallback to python3-venv and pip, and unify colored output and process management
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: outline project planning and reporting workflows
- Add a Project Planning Structure section to both copilot-instructions and agents docs, outlining the `.github/plans` directory with Backlogs and Bugs subfolders and their roles. - Introduce a Work Report Protocol that mandates creating immutable, templated reports in `.github/reports` after each task. - Replace the long list of specific backlog entries in AGENTS.md with a concise overview of the Backlogs and Bugs directories. - Tweak the debug logging note in AGENTS.md to a shorter “Use util.printD() for debug output.”
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: enhance Civitai User Gallery generate info display
- Enhanced on_gallery_select function to extract generation parameters from Civitai API metadata - Added UUID extraction from filename to lookup metadata from _current_page_metadata - Implemented proper formatting of prompt, negativePrompt, sampler, and cfgScale parameters - Added comprehensive debug logging to trace execution flow and identify issues - Enhanced get_user_gallery to store metadata with detailed debug output - All 327 tests pass, maintaining full compatibility with existing functionality - Resolves issue where clicking gallery images did not display generation parameters
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix(gallery): ensure Generate Info displays for user gallery image selection
When a user selects an image in the Civitai User Gallery, ensure the local file path is passed to PNG info extraction logic, not a URL. This fixes the blank Generate Info bug. All tests pass. See report 026 for details.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs(plan): add centralized Civitai HTTP client backlog and implementation plan
Add detailed backlog and planning documents for implementing a centralized HTTP client for all Civitai API requests. The plan covers core client creation, refactoring modules, error handling, integration testing, performance, and documentation. All items are written in zh-TW with English for code and comments, following project conventions.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: handle evt.value list format in gallery selects
- Fix TypeError: unhashable type: 'list' in gallery select handlers - Add defensive type checking in recipe and classification functions - Support both string and list formats from Gradio gallery components - Add comprehensive test coverage for evt.value handling - Ensure graceful degradation for invalid input types
The issue occurred when Gradio gallery components returned evt.value as [image_url, shortcut_name] instead of just the shortcut name string. Functions expecting string keys for dictionary lookups would crash when receiving list inputs.
Solution implements two-layer defense: 1. Event handlers extract correct value based on input type 2. Utility functions validate input types before use
Resolves crashes in recipe and classification workflows while maintaining backward compatibility.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

refactor: revamp reporting workflow and boost path logging
- Overhaul the project report guide by renaming it to Civitai Shortcut, dropping the simple template, switching examples and checks from Rust/cargo to Python (black, flake8, pytest), and enforcing three-digit report IDs - Remove the deprecated simple report template file - In the main REPORT_TEMPLATE, swap cargo and llvm-cov commands for black, flake8, pytest coverage steps and update example file listings to Python scripts and requirements.txt - Add util.printD debug logs to every path-retrieval method in standalone_path_manager for better tracing - Refactor webui_path_manager’s util import block by inlining spec_from_file_location arguments and tidying up mock module setup
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: handle Gradio SelectData list format in gallery events
- Enhanced get_modelid_from_shortcutname() to handle both string and list inputs - Fixed AttributeError in gallery select event handlers across multiple modules - Added comprehensive input validation and error handling - Created test suite with 11 test cases covering all scenarios - Maintains backward compatibility while adding robust error handling
Fixes crashes when evt.value is returned as list [image_url, shortcut_name] instead of expected string format from Gradio Gallery SelectData events.
Affected modules: - scripts/civitai_manager_libs/setting.py - scripts/civitai_manager_libs/recipe_action.py - scripts/civitai_manager_libs/classification_action.py - scripts/civitai_manager_libs/recipe_browser_page.py
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

refactor(test): remove legacy conftest.py and improve UI adapter test isolation
- Remove obsolete conftest.py which caused pytest plugin errors and is no longer needed for test execution - Refactor tests/test_ui_adapter.py to fully mock all UI action modules, preventing Gradio context errors and improving test reliability - Ensure ui_adapter.py docstrings and style conform to PEP 8 and project linting requirements - All changes pass black and flake8 linting as well as pytest suite
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix(recipe): enhance Prompt Recipe name validation and warning feedback

- Add input validation in on_recipe_create_btn_click to show gr.Warning when name is empty, whitespace-only, or default value
- Update function docstring to describe validation and return behavior
- Add pytest unit tests for name validation scenarios
- Wrap setting._initialize_extension_base in try/except to avoid import errors in test environments
- Stub gradio, PIL, and requests modules in conftest for test imports
- Add detailed job report document for Bug Fix #024
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs(plan): add detailed plan for Prompt Recipe name validation and user notification\n\nAdd a comprehensive development plan for improving Prompt Recipe name validation and user feedback using gr.Warning. The plan includes technical analysis, implementation steps, testing strategy, and acceptance criteria.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: resolve Civitai User Gallery PNG info extraction issue
- Fixed logical error in on_civitai_hidden_change function where premature return prevented fallback mechanisms - Added comprehensive three-tier fallback system (compatibility layer -> WebUI -> PIL direct) - Improved error handling and logging for better debugging - Fixed parameters_copypaste conditional import to prevent undefined name errors - Enhanced standalone mode support with proper type checking and temp file management - Standardized exception handling across all fallback mechanisms - Fixed code style issues (flake8/black compliance)
The issue was caused by a return statement that prevented fallback code execution, resulting in blank Generate Info display when clicking images in Civitai User Gallery. Users can now successfully view PNG metadata information for gallery images.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

test: configure pytest as project test runner
- Introduce a key directive to use pytest for running tests and ensure the project is testable.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: resolve gallery select AttributeError with list input
- Add type checking in on_sc_gallery_select to handle both list and string evt.value formats - Support new Gradio gallery SelectData format [image_url, shortcut_name] - Maintain backward compatibility with existing string format - Add comprehensive error handling and logging for unexpected formats
Fixes issue where clicking gallery images caused AttributeError: 'list' object has no attribute 'rfind'
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: correct PNG info extraction for Generate prompt from image feature
- Fix extract_png_info return value handling in recipe_action.py - Fix similar issues in ishortcut_action.py and civitai_gallery_action.py - Extract only parameters string from tuple instead of entire result - Add debug logging for better troubleshooting - Generate prompt from image feature now works correctly - All existing tests continue to pass
Resolves issue where dragging images to Generate Prompt From Image section would result in blank prompts instead of extracted metadata.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: simplify doc paths and require report templates
- Simplify core reference paths by removing leading `../` prefixes in documentation instructions - Clarify report step: explicitly write reports following `.github/reports/README.md` and `.github/reports/REPORT_TEMPLATE.md` before committing alongside code changes
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: enhance metadata processor to support PIL Image inputs
- Update IMetadataProcessor interface to accept Union[str, Image.Image] - Implement smart input handling in standalone and WebUI adapters - Add comprehensive test coverage for PIL Image processing - Maintain full backward compatibility with string path inputs - Improve performance by avoiding temporary files in standalone mode
Fixes PIL.UnidentifiedImageError and TypeError in standalone mode when Gradio UI passes PIL Image objects to extract_png_info()
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: improve linting to auto fix errors and warnings
- Clarify linting step to fix both errors and styling warnings (not just errors) when running black and flake8.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: safely hide civitai UI on missing tab events
- Add a guard in _on_civitai_tabs_select to early-return when evt is None, log a debug message, and hide all related UI components.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

refactor: enhance test imports and unify compatibility layer
- Add the project’s “scripts” folder to pytest’s import path in conftest.py. - Consolidate compatibility‐layer access by importing CompatibilityLayer everywhere and replacing custom get_compatibility_layer functions with CompatibilityLayer.get_compatibility_layer(). - In webui_path_manager, mock out WebUI modules during tests, load util via importlib to avoid relative‐import issues, and simplify all get_* methods to return their values directly (removing intermediate variables and debug prints). - Apply consistent multiline formatting (with trailing commas) to all Gradio UI component constructors across action modules for readability. - Update regex helpers in util.py to use raw‐string literals for matching URLs and width parameters. - In tests, switch from legacy get_compatibility_layer/reset_compatibility_layer imports to CompatibilityLayer.get_compatibility_layer and CompatibilityLayer.reset_compatibility_layer, and adjust fixtures accordingly.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: enable restart, unify compatibility, and refine UI
- Add psutil>=5.9.0 to requirements to support standalone process restart - Refactor compatibility layer by moving the global instance into a class-level `_compat_layer`, implementing static `get_compatibility_layer`/`reset_compatibility_layer`, and pruning legacy exports - Replace all calls to `setting.get_compatibility_layer` with `CompatibilityLayer.get_compatibility_layer` across modules for unified mode detection - Standardize Gradio callback signatures and formatting in prompt_ui and setting_action (expanded multiline parameters/returns, consistent f-strings and blank lines) - In setting_action, add standalone restart logic that closes open file handles and re-executes the process via psutil and os.execl - Enhance civitai_shortcut_action with new UI event handlers (NSFW toggles, tab selections, gallery/model ID updates, model folder refresh, URL/text uploads) and improved debug logging
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: remove reference loop of logging
- Clean up setting.py imports by moving import_manager below util and removing repeated in-function util imports - In setting.py, update extension_base initialization to call path_manager.get_extension_path instead of get_base_path - Remove util’s compatibility-layer helper and overhaul printD to always output messages with a fixed “[Civitai Shortcut]” prefix, dropping its conditional debug logic and force parameter
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat(logging): enhance debug tracing in all path manager methods
- Add debug logging statements to all path getter methods to print their computed values, using util.printD for improved traceability during execution. - Add detailed debug logging statements throughout the module to trace path and import-related operations, including import successes and failures, as well as the results of all path retrieval methods. - Remove a debug print statement from the get_compatibility_layer function to clean up console output.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>
